## AUDIENCE INTELLIGENCE
*(Sourced from: TikTok comments, beauty forum discussions, Quora threads, community product reviews, editorial comment sections, nail tech professional forums — Reddit inaccessible, compensated via wider cross-channel synthesis)*

### Top 5 Pain Points

1. **"Will almond suit MY hands?"** — The single most repeated anxiety. Readers with wide nail beds, short fingers, or "chubby" hands fear the shape will look wrong on them. Competitors give generic reassurance; nobody gives the specific, honest breakdown by hand type.
2. **"I don't have the length — do I need extensions?"** — Consistent confusion about minimum natural nail length needed vs when acrylic/Gel X is required. Many assume almond is impossible on natural short nails.
3. **"How do I stop them breaking?"** — Especially from first-time almond wearers or people switching from squoval/square. Fear of the tapered tip as a fragility point drives hesitation.
4. **"Acrylic or gel for almond shape — what's actually better?"** — Very common pre-appointment question. Audiences are overwhelmed by the system options (acrylic, Gel X, hard gel, polygel) with no clear almond-specific guidance.
5. **"Are almond nails high-maintenance / not practical for daily life?"** — Working women, active lifestyles, keyboard users questioning whether the shape is "too much" for their day-to-day. Short almond's 2026 breakout is directly answering this but most pillar posts haven't caught up.

### User Sentiment
Aspirational with underlying hesitation — they *want* almond nails (the aesthetic is highly desirable) but are unsure they can pull it off practically or physically.

